<br>
For anyone that has not been to scarlet desert<br>
Info from one night in the desert.<br>
<br>
about 7 types of mobs<br>
Tro Jeg warriors  (non Kos)<br>
Bloodtribe (non kos)<br>
<br>
if you leave the trojeg, and the bloodtribe alone,<br>
it's a fairly safe zone<br>
<br>
i hunted the below mobs<br>
without  any issues or major risks at all.<br>
along the western half of the northen wall<br>
along the western half of the southern wall<br>
along the entire western wall (grey zone)<br>
crawlers   (kos)<br>
sunflowers   (kos)<br>
rockhoppers     (kos)<br>
sun reavers (&amp; reverants)   (kos)<br>
cheetahs  (kos)<br>
<br>
BUT I hear the aggro radius is huge if you start wacking the trojeg  or the bloodtribe.<br>
<br>
the blood tribe occupy all kinds of little tunnels.<br>
they are the only mobs i saw in the 7 or so tunnels i looked in.<br>
<br>
I got good  safe exp (in level 52)<br>
while raising my peircing skill to about 87  from 35.<br>
if my skill was maxed it would have been even easier.<br>
<br>
this might be really good for level 47 to 51<br>
alot of blues but alot of lightblues at  52.<br>
after 53 probably WAaaaaaay too many light blues and greens<br>
Jook<br>
